Analysis.name: Adverse events
Subgroup: RCT: early ≤ 10 days vs late > 10 days
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: There were no deviations from intended interventions, patients were blinded and an appropriate analysis was used to estimate the effect of assignment to intervention.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Outcome data was available for all patients
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Outcome assessors were not blinded. Thus, assessment of the outcome could have been influenced by knowledge of intervention received.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Selection of reported results was done appropriately, a research protocol was prepared
Overall.bias.support: No information regarding allocation concealment was available and outcome assessors were not blinded.
